title: Sermanni departs Matildas pinching himself after 'phenomenal' privilege
summary: Tom Sermanni has paid tribute to the "phenomenal" crowds who support the Matildas after his final game in charge of the women's national team. Australia's 4-1 win over Argentina marked his 151st game as coach or interim coach of the Matildas, in stints dating back to 1994. Joe Montemurro now takes over as Matildas coach from the Scottish-born Sermanni.

title: 'Something new to me': Kasatkina praises Aussie fans after French Open exit
summary: Daria Kasatkina lost to Mirra Andreeva 6-3, 7-5 to bow out of the French Open. The new Australian paid tribute to her Aussie fans, saying the support was not something she had felt before.

title: Minimum wage to rise above inflation, ASX rises — as it happened
summary: Australian shares have closed higher . Minimum and award wages will lift 3.5 per cent from July 1 . Prices current around 4:35pm AEST .

title: Trump tariff uncertainty brings weaker outlook for Australia, RBA official says
summary: The amount of uncertainty in the global economy about Donald Trump's tariffs has contributed to a weaker outlook for Australia's economy, a Reserve Bank official says. Assistant governor Sarah Hunter said Australia was unlikely to face direct negative impacts.

title: 'Can't walk': Heartbreaking Ozzy Osbourne update
summary: Sharon Osbourne said the band’s long-awaited reunion was emotional for her husband . Ozzy Osbourne can no longer walk due to the worsening of his Parkinson's disease . ‘Parkinson’'s is a progressive disease,’ she said .
